During the course will be creating an overview about national curriculum in different levels, curriculums in kindergartens and schools, individual development and learning plans, and about the implementation of curriculum for special need children. Also will be introducing the basics and procedure of development the individual development and learning plans, and how the curriculum implementation process and assessment of results should look like.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To complement of students knowledge's about curriculum planning for special need children both in kindergarten and school, to develop skills of curriculum planning and supervise the curriculum planning in different levels.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After taking the course a student: 1.Knows national curriculums in different levels. 2.Is able to take into consideration different target groups in curriculum implementation.  3.Is able to develop individual development and learning plan.  4.Is able to supervise the planning of individual development and learning plan.
